    Note: The class description below has been excerpted from the Hl7 2.3.1 documentation. Sectional references made below also refer to the same documentation. Format: YYYY[MM[DD]] In prior versions of HL7, this data type was always specified to be in the format YYYYMMDD. In the current and future versions, the precision of a date may be expressed by limiting the number of digits used with the format specification YYYY[MM[DD]]. Thus, YYYY is used to specify a precision of "year," YYYYMM specifies a precision of "month," and YYYYMMDD specifies a precision of "day." By site-specific agreement, YYYYMMDD may be used where backward compatibility must be maintained. Examples: |19880704| |199503|
    Author:
    Neal Acharya
